<%#
kind: PXEGrub
name: Jumpstart default PXEGrub
model: ProvisioningTemplate
oses:
- Solaris
description: |
  The template to render Grub bootloader configuration for Solaris.
  The output is deployed on the host's subnet TFTP proxy.
  This template is for legacy Grub 1.x, you are probably looking for Grub2.
-%>
default=0
timeout=10
title Solaris_10 Jumpstart
        kernel <%= @host.multiboot %> kernel/unix - install dhcp nowin -B install_config=<%= @host.jumpstart_path %>,sysid_config=<%= @host.jumpstart_path %>/sysidcfg/sysidcfg_primary,install_media=<%= @host.install_path %>,install_boot=<%= @host.install_path %>/boot
        module <%= @host.miniroot %>
title Solaris 10
        findroot (rootfs0,0,a)
        kernel$ /platform/i86pc/multiboot
        module /platform/i86pc/boot_archive
